Overview
========

XtalOpt searches for the global minimum of a crystal structure's
PES using a evolutionary algorithm. It is implemented as an extension
to the Avogadro molecular editor and licensed under the GPL v2 or later.

More information can be found at http://xtalopt.openmolecules.net.



Installation
============

FOR ARCHLINUX...
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
An up-to-date copy of the installation instructions is maintained at:

http://xtalopt.openmolecules.net/wiki/index.fcgi/wiki/Installation

There is also a tutorial available at:

http://xtalopt.openmolecules.net/globalsearch/docs/tut-xo.html


FOR UBUNTU 12.04 OR LATER...
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
    
    sudo apt-get install -f build-essential cmake doxygen git libcairo2 libwxgtk2.8-0 libxml2 libeigen* libqt4* qt4* openssh* ssh subversion wx-common zlib1g

    mkdir ~/src

    cd ~/src

OpenBabel
---------
    git clone https://github.com/zfalls/OpenBabel.git openbabel

    mkdir openbabel/build
    cd openbabel/build

    cmake .. -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=$HOME -DBUILD_GUI=FALSE

    make -j3

    sudo make install

Avogadro
--------
    cd ~/src

    git clone https://github.com/zfalls/Avogadro.git avogadro

    mkdir avogadro/build

    cd  avogadro/build

    cmake .. -DOPENBABEL2_INCLUDE_DIR=$HOME/include/openbabel-2.0 -DOPENBABEL2_LIBRARIES=$HOME/lib/libopenbabel.so -DENABLE_PYTHON=false -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=$HOME

    make -j3

    sudo make install

XtalOpt
-------
    cd ~/src

    git clone -b master https://github.com/zfalls/XtalOpt.git xtalopt

    mkdir xtalopt/build

    cd xtalopt/build

    cmake .. -DOPENBABEL2_INCLUDE_DIR=$HOME/include/openbabel-2.0 -DOPENBABEL2_LIBRARIES=$HOME/lib/libopenbabel.so -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=$HOME ***

        ***Options***
            
            -DENABLE_RANDOMDOCK=1

            -DENABLE_GAPC=1

    make -j3

    sudo make install


EVRYTHING SHOULD BE READY TO GO!!!
    As long as $HOME/bin is in your $PATH, you can run avogadro by typing

        avogadro &

    in the command line



